	<str name="Title">
		Method for preparing acidic solutions of activated silica for water treatment
	</str>
	<str name="Abstract">
		A process is disclosed for the production of acidic solutions of activated silica for water treatment. Activated silica is formed during the process of acidifying a sodium silicate solution to below pH 2 with sulfuric acid.
